summary: I’m still bitter about Ed Sheeran on Game of Thrones. We could have had No Feather Bed for me, but we got Hands of Gold. How is...
body: I’m still bitter about Ed Sheeran on Game of Thrones. We could have had No Feather Bed for me, but we got Hands of Gold. How is that song even relevant to Arya? It’s a song about Tyrion and Shae, it has nothing to do with her! That was such a waste of a cameo.

summary: People can try to say that Arya does not have a big role to play in the end of ASoIaF, but George R.R. Martin himself said...
body:
People can try to say that Arya does not have a big role to play in the end of ASoIaF, but George R.R. Martin himself said that “If a twelve year old has to conquer the world then so be it.”

And that quote could only refer to Shireen or Arya because unless he suddenly introduces a new character who will be 12 in TWoW they are the only ones who fit that criteria.

summary: The amount of people who acknowledge that Arya would fight against a marriage is a pretty solid amount. I mean three different...
body:
The amount of people who acknowledge that Arya would fight against a marriage is a pretty solid amount. I mean three different people, three people who actually would have known her, out right say she would refuse. 

“Robb was to marry one of their aunts, and Arya one of their uncles. “She never will,” Bran said, “not Arya,” but Maester Luwin was unyielding, so there they were beside Rickon.” - Bran III, ACoK 

“He’s to marry Arya Stark. My little sister.” Jon could almost see her in that moment, long-faced and gawky, all knobby knees and sharp elbows, with her dirty face and tangled hair. They would wash the one and comb the other, he did not doubt, but he could not imagine Arya in a wedding gown, nor Ramsay Bolton’s bed. No matter how afraid she is, she will not show it. If he tries to lay a hand on her, she’ll fight him.” - Jon VI, ADwD 

“Lord Ramsay.” The girl dipped down before him. That was wrong as well. The real Arya Stark would have spat into his face. “I pray that I will make you a good wife and give you strong sons to follow after you.” - Reek II, ADwD

The funny thing about this is that when it comes to Sansa people believe her wed…mainly because they are older and understand she does not have a choice in the matter. Arya on the other hand does not believe that Sansa could have wed Tyrion. 

“That’s stupid, Arya thought. Sansa only knows songs, not spells, and she’d never marry the Imp.” - Arya XIII, ASoS 

I can’t decide if she means they never would wed Sansa to Tyrion or Sansa would refuse. Personally i think she thinks the latter. There was no way her sister would allow herself to wed Tyrion Lannister. I think this is one of those moments where we see Arya’s childhood naivety (of course her sister wont marry Tyrion, no one would dare force her) and it is a moment where we get to see how she views her sister. Sansa, the pre-war version Arya knew, would refuse. 

Does this mean anything? In the grand scheme of things, not really. As someone who loves the Stark Sisters, though, it is an interesting moment to see that Arya does not believe her sister to be someone to just follow orders; she views her sister as someone who will refuse and she seems to be the only person who thinks she would refuse. But Arya is right Sansa does try to refuse, she even tries to run.  

“You can’t make me.”

“Of course we can. You may come along quietly and say your vows as befits a lady, or you may struggle and scream and make a spectacle for the stableboys to titter over, but you will end up wedded and bedded all the same.” The queen opened the door.

Ser Meryn Trant and Ser Osmund Kettleblack were waiting without, in the white scale armor of the Kingsguard. “Escort Lady Sansa to the sept,” she told them. “Carry her if you must, but try not to tear the gown, it was very costly.” Sansa tried to run, but Cersei’s handmaid caught her before she’d gone a yard. 

- Sansa III, ASoS 

Arya is the only one to think that Sansa would fight back like that. I think that in a lot of ways Arya does not think her sister weak. She may not always like her and there is a lot of resentment there, but she does not seem to think of Sansa as someone who would give up without a fight.

summary: It just occurred to me that, if he survived Season 1, Ned wouldn't be very proud of his children (and the ones he raised as...
body:
It just occurred to me that, if he survived Season 1, Ned wouldn’t be very proud of his children (and the ones he raised as his).

Robb broke the promise to a lord which had given him support.

Jon broke his vow to the Night’s Watch.

Theon, of course, betrayed his all family.

Sansa got Ramsey eaten alive by his dogs.

Arya killed two people and had their father eat them.

Of course, all of them had their path, their reasons, their sufferings, and some of these acts were a well deserved revenge. But none of this was Ned’s way. He was all about duty and honour, respecting his enemies and keeping his promises no matter what.

body:

Fandom: Game of Thrones

Rating: Mature (for sex)

Summary: Arya Stark returns to Winterfell to discover they have a new bastard smith, and he has a new daughter who likes to play with swords.

Link: https://archiveofourown.org/works/2479127

Review: I felt this was very true to what could have happened in Game of Thrones if Gendry had a child. I loved the relationship shown between Arya and Gendry, the banter and how their relationship alters a bit years after they last saw each other (the Brotherhood in this fic).
